  ],
  "published": "2018-12-21",
  "runtimeMin": 40,
  "format": "Sean Fennessey and David Shoemaker run an exit survey on 'Aquaman,' James Wan's DC detour: the most beautiful superhero movie yet, welded to dialogue they figure a 14-year-old wrote. Then they look ahead at the DC slate: Shazam!, Birds of Prey, and a Cyborg movie nobody asked for.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "'Aquaman': the exit survey",
      "note": "good, not great, and trying to be six movies at once",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Aquaman",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Both land on 'good, not great.' James Wan directs it as purposeful schlock (bad dialogue, psychedelic set pieces), and the hosts count six films it's cribbing from at once. They call the CGI undersea work the most beautiful in any superhero movie, with the trench sequence and its flare as the single best shot, but the surface scenes look faker and the straightforward story drags once you can see every beat coming. Jason Momoa recast as a 'rock' instead of the blond, chiseled Arthur; Patrick Wilson as half-brother Orm; Nicole Kidman underused; Dolph Lundgren stiffening the mythology; the Sicily trident detour is the designated popcorn/bathroom-break stretch. Julie Andrews voices the giant sea creature at the climax."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The DC slate ahead",
      "note": "what comes after Aquaman",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Shazam!",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Due April 2019, from horror director David Sandberg. The hosts expect a jokier, teen, almost-Netflix tone, and note the character's odd tension with Superman (originally a rival Captain Marvel)."
        },
        {
          "title": "Birds of Prey",
          "year": 2020,
          "note": "Margot Robbie developing and starring, first-time feature director Cathy Yan. Framed as low-IP-risk, high-star bet: extend Harley Quinn without a 10-picture lock-in. Cast floated: Mary Elizabeth Winstead, Jurnee Smollett-Bell, Rosie Perez. Sean reads the full parenthetical title aloud."
        },
        {
          "title": "Dead Pigs",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Cathy Yan's feature before Birds of Prey, cited as why handing her a tentpole reads as a risk."
        },
        {
          "title": "Suicide Squad",
          "year": 2016,
          "note": "Where Harley Quinn / Margot Robbie came from; the template for luring big stars into DC at low IP risk (the Will Smith model)."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
